> Barley is the OG. It's one of the earliest domesticated grains, yet its chewy texture and nutty flavor are still a favorite. In these spicy veggie bowls, our chefs opted for quick-cooking pearled barley as a hearty base for harissa-roasted zucchini, bell pepper, and onion. A classic chermoula and lemon yogurt are drizzled over top, then everything's sprinkled with feta, toasted almonds, and golden raisins. If you like, mix everything together for barley in every bite!

== Barley ==

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 4 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees.

In a #small pot{}, combine @pearl barley{3/4%cup}, 2 1/2 cups water (4 cups for 4), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer and cover. Cook until barley is tender and water has absorbed, ~{25-30%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in step 6.

> If you end up with any excess water, simply pour it out. Alternatively, if water evaporates before barley is done, add a splash of water.

== Prep ==

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into 1/2-inch-thick half-moons. Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1}. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Pick @cilantro{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves.

== Roasted Veggies ==

Toss zucchini, bell pepper, and onion on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, 3/4 tsp @harissa powder{1%tbsp}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. (Be sure to measure the harissa powder—we sent more! Use less if you prefer less heat.)

Roast on top rack until veggies are tender and browned, ~{15-18%minutes}. (For 4, divide between 2 baking sheets; roast on top and middle racks.)

== Lemon Yogurt ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @yogurt{4%tbsp} and a big pinch of lemon zest. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Chermoula ==

In a separate small bowl, combine cilantro, @olive oil{1 1/2%tbsp}, @garlic powder{1/4%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), a squeeze of lemon juice, and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%tsp} to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

== Toasted Almonds ==

Heat a #small dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce} and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove pan from heat.

== Serving ==

Drain any excess water from barley if necessary; fluff with a #fork{}. Stir in @veggie stock concentrate{2}, @golden raisins{1%ounce}, remaining @garlic powder{3/4%tsp}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and as much remaining lemon zest as you like. Season with salt and pepper.

Stir half the roasted veggies into pot with barley.

Divide barley mixture between #bowls{}; top with remaining veggies, @feta cheese{1/2%cup}, and almonds. Drizzle with lemon yogurt and chermoula. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges and remaining chili flakes on the side.